    "summary": "Hans de Wit is Director of the Center for International Higher Education (CIHE) at Boston College. Before he was director of the Centre for Higher Education Internationalisation (CHEI) at the Universita Cattolica Sacro Cuore, Milan, Italy and Professor of Internationalisation of Higher Education  at the Amsterdam University of Applied Sciences. He is Research Associate with Nelson Mandela Metropolitan University\u2019s Unit for Higher Education Internationalisation in the Developing World, Port South Africa.\n\nHe is the Founding Editor of the \u2018Journal of Studies in International Education\u2019. He has a Monthly blog at University World News, associate editor of International Higher Education and member of the editorial board of Policy Reviews in Higher Education and RUSC, Universities and Knowledge Society Journal. He has published widely on International Higher Education.   \n\nIn 2005-2006 He was a New Century Scholar of the Fulbright Program Higher Education in the 21st Century, and in 1995 and 2006 a visiting scholar in the USA and in 2002 in Australia. \n\nHe has been among others Vice-President for International Affairs at the Universiteit van Amsterdam, in the period 1986-2005. He has a bachelor, master and PhD from the University of Amsterdam.\n\nHe is founding member and past president of the European Association for International Education (EAIE). He received awards from the University of Amsterdam (2006), AIEA (2006 and 2013), AMPEI (2014), CIEE (2004 and 2006), NAFSA (2002) and EAIE (1999 and 2008).\n\nSpecialties: Professor and Consultant in International Education Research and Management, regional expertise in Europe, Northern and Latin America and the Asia Pacific region, quality reviews, institutional strategies, project and program evaluation, author of books, studies and articles, etc.",
